The paper deals with range spaces, which are a fundamental concept in computational geometry and discrete mathematics. The paper presents improved upper bounds for the size of relative (p,Epsilon)-approximation for well-behaved range spaces, which are a subclass of range spaces with certain properties. This makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) the most likely categories. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely categories. Lastly, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible category.
